      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Substantive due process is a vital constitutional safeguard that protects fundamental liberties against government overreach. It ensures that the government cannot infringe upon deeply rooted rights, even if those rights aren't explicitly listed in the Constitution. This doctrine has been crucial in expanding civil rights by striking down laws that unjustly limit personal autonomy and liberty. It is a powerful check on government power, ensuring individual freedom remains paramount.",
